to the movement
for black lives.

04:06.780 --> 04:08.530
The value of an image.

04:10.534 --> 04:13.235
Is the one
with the dollar amount

04:13.270 --> 04:17.906
worth more than the
one that brought peace
to a grieving family?

04:22.279 --> 04:24.363
We can talk about the details
on nfts later.

04:24.398 --> 04:26.581
Right now,
let's just go over the basics.

04:26.616 --> 04:28.583
What is an nft?

04:28.618 --> 04:31.370
It stands
for non-fungible token.

04:31.405 --> 04:34.756
It's a one-of-a-kind piece
of digital art stored online,

04:34.791 --> 04:36.675
secured on the blockchain.

04:36.727 --> 04:41.463
Artists buy and sell nfts
to make a living all the time.

04:41.482 --> 04:47.269
But whatever value an image
may have comes first from you,
the photographer.

04:48.739 --> 04:54.026
All you have
to offer as artists
is your perspective.

04:54.078 --> 04:57.946
So, I want you all to show me
the world through your eyes.

05:01.085 --> 05:02.334
Show me you.

05:04.672 --> 05:08.790
The first nft was minted on
may 3rd, 2014.

05:09.993 --> 05:12.344
