09:59.399 --> 10:01.566
Hedonism. 1999.

10:01.602 --> 10:03.602
-Oh, dear.
-Ocho rios.

10:03.637 --> 10:05.737
Oh, oh. I found it.
Look at this.

10:05.772 --> 10:07.972
Oh, here we go. Yes.

10:07.991 --> 10:09.691
Oh.

10:09.743 --> 10:11.309
Boom! Boom!

10:11.328 --> 10:12.777
[in jamaican accent]
how do I look, man?

10:12.812 --> 10:14.446
Keep the hat,
but lose the accent.

10:14.481 --> 10:16.081
-Don't do me like that,
prosper.
-[prosper] oh.

10:16.116 --> 10:18.583
Come on now. [laughs]

10:19.836 --> 10:20.952
yeah.

10:20.987 --> 10:22.587
Thanks again for everything,
wood.

10:22.623 --> 10:24.706
There's no way I could have
done this all by myself.

10:24.758 --> 10:27.292
We're just so glad that
sandra make you so happy.

10:27.327 --> 10:28.843
Do anything
to keep that going.

10:32.015 --> 10:33.131
[sighs]

10:34.434 --> 10:35.917
you know,
that's always a good thing

10:35.952 --> 10:38.803
when you got two good people
and they into each other.

10:40.190 --> 10:43.558
Sometimes you just got
to dig deep, go through it.

10:43.610 --> 10:46.611
But when you do, there's
nothing better than love.

10:46.647 --> 10:48.012
Mmm-hmm.

10:48.031 --> 10:49.347
Yeah, you're right about that.

10:49.366 --> 10:51.015
It's about time
you got off the market.

10:51.034 --> 10:52.350
No more flying solo.

10:52.369 --> 10:53.635
Oh. Yeah.

10:53.670 --> 10:56.504
I've been solo
for a long time.

10:56.540 --> 10:58.356
I kind of got used
to being alone.

10:58.375 --> 11:00.408
Oh, man.
Nobody needs to be alone.

11:00.460 --> 11:02.811
Sometimes it just
takes a moment
to find your better half.

11:02.846 --> 11:06.831
Look, I tried for a long time,
but I found my queen.

11:06.866 --> 11:08.667
Claire was my better half.

11:08.702 --> 11:09.834
Yeah.

11:09.869 --> 11:11.419
The only woman I ever loved.

11:11.471 --> 11:13.705
Thought it was forever.

11:13.724 --> 11:16.758
Didn't think I'd need
to be out here looking again.

11:16.810 --> 11:18.143
I was a little rusty.

11:18.178 --> 11:21.713
You know, back then,
it didn't have to be smooth,

11:21.732 --> 11:23.381
know the right words
to say it,

11:23.400 --> 11:26.334
just being me was enough.

11:26.370 --> 11:27.885
No, it still is.

11:27.904 --> 11:30.605
Hey, being real
is never going out of style.

11:30.657 --> 11:32.357
Well, I hope you're right

11:33.994 --> 11:35.527
'cause I'm sweet on sandy.

11:39.065 --> 11:40.865
I was born into it.

11:40.900 --> 11:42.667
Both sides
of my family were farmers,

11:42.703 --> 11:43.868
cherokee and african.

11:45.038 --> 11:47.872
From day one,
all I ever wanted to do.

11:49.009 --> 11:52.010
Take care of the land,
it takes care of us.

11:52.045 --> 11:53.294
You native american?

11:53.346 --> 11:55.180
Both. And neither.

11:55.215 --> 11:56.581
Depending on who you talk to.

11:56.600 --> 11:58.550
Not black enough
or indian enough for some.

11:59.720 --> 12:01.436
I don't always fit in either.

12:03.523 --> 12:06.024
That little pouch
that you gave my brother
of the seeds,

12:07.394 --> 12:09.728
that's a beautiful way
to honor your mother.

12:09.763 --> 12:11.613
The seeds remember
the land they came from.

12:12.883 --> 12:13.982
My mother used
to tell us about

12:14.017 --> 12:17.101
how girls would braid rice
and okra into the hair

12:17.120 --> 12:20.205
when they were stolen
from africa to remember home.

12:20.240 --> 12:21.322
Yeah.

12:21.374 --> 12:24.042
Lots of african plants
and crops were here

12:24.077 --> 12:26.044
in the americas
because of those women.

12:27.214 --> 12:30.048
You know, our mother would
tell us the story

12:30.083 --> 12:32.083
of when her people
were removed from their land,

12:32.118 --> 12:34.219
they took their seeds
with them to oklahoma,

12:34.254 --> 12:36.087
but the crops
wouldn't grow there.

12:36.122 --> 12:38.757
And the white settlers' food
wasn't growing here either,

12:38.792 --> 12:42.677
so the white people begged
our people for seeds to grow

12:42.729 --> 12:45.013
food and survive, right?

12:45.065 --> 12:48.650
Our people deliberated
and ultimately
they shared them.

12:50.153 --> 12:54.806
But you see, the seeds needed
to be in their soil,

12:54.825 --> 12:57.609
where they came
from in order to survive.

12:57.644 --> 12:58.777
Mmm-hmm.

12:59.946 --> 13:01.279
I feel that.

13:01.314 --> 13:02.914
[phone buzzes]

13:08.455 --> 13:11.322
so true story, nova,

13:11.341 --> 13:14.659
you got someone tending
your garden at home
waiting on you?

13:14.678 --> 13:15.960
Well, not at the moment.

13:16.797 --> 13:18.429
He's out of town.
But yeah, I do.

13:20.183 --> 13:21.466
You?

13:23.336 --> 13:25.169
I'm still looking.

13:25.188 --> 13:26.471
But good for you.

13:31.645 --> 13:33.278
Hmm.

13:33.313 --> 13:34.846
Okay, shall we?

13:34.865 --> 13:35.980
What you got?

13:36.015 --> 13:37.615
