13:52.883 --> 13:54.182
Yeah.

13:55.552 --> 13:58.169
Hey, while I have you,

13:58.204 --> 13:59.838
I wanted to show you
some of my photos

13:59.873 --> 14:02.140
for the art show
for end of the summer?

14:02.175 --> 14:04.259
Sure.
Let's see what you got.

14:04.311 --> 14:06.227
Working hard on some stuff,
you know?

14:10.233 --> 14:11.816
Hmm.

14:11.852 --> 14:13.351
Some of my recent stuff.

14:14.404 --> 14:16.387
-Mostly black and white.
-Mmm.

14:16.406 --> 14:17.889
I like it.

14:17.908 --> 14:19.157
I see you coming through.

14:20.660 --> 14:22.527
-This is nice work, michael.
-Thank you.

14:23.663 --> 14:25.730
I really want to be
a part of the art show.

14:25.749 --> 14:26.831
You should talk to keke.

14:26.867 --> 14:28.366
She's curating.

14:28.401 --> 14:30.067
Oh.

14:30.086 --> 14:31.536
Oh, I didn't know.

14:33.239 --> 14:34.539
I...

14:35.842 --> 14:37.375
I don't know
if she told you, but--

14:37.410 --> 14:39.210
yeah, she told me.

14:39.245 --> 14:40.678
She's the boss.

14:40.714 --> 14:42.013
So, you got to weigh in.

14:43.850 --> 14:45.049
See you in class.

14:56.112 --> 14:58.613
You're looking like a cat
that swallowed a canary.

14:59.766 --> 15:00.865
Well, I don't want to brag,

15:00.901 --> 15:04.035
but we did sell out
all of my pies today.

15:04.070 --> 15:06.487
Yeah, there were a lot
of tourists in here today,

15:06.539 --> 15:07.772
but the rest of them?

15:07.791 --> 15:12.994
Nah, they like real butter,
cream, and sugar.

15:13.046 --> 15:15.446
No substitutes, baby.

15:15.465 --> 15:18.633
Substitutes can be tasty
if you know what you're doing.

15:20.720 --> 15:22.086
I can show you a few tricks.

15:25.225 --> 15:27.058
All right, mr. I can show you.

15:28.979 --> 15:32.063
You can help me whip up
a jamaican feast

15:32.098 --> 15:33.564
for prosper's big date.

15:37.971 --> 15:40.104
We'll see. [chuckles]

15:40.974 --> 15:43.024
plantains are my specialty.

15:43.076 --> 15:44.242
My mom taught me.

15:44.277 --> 15:46.310
Did you tell her
that I asked about her?

15:46.329 --> 15:47.445
How is she?

15:49.282 --> 15:50.415
She's good.

15:50.450 --> 15:52.250
Just busy working.

15:54.654 --> 15:56.337
You would tell me
if there was a problem, right?

15:57.607 --> 15:58.773
Of course.

16:00.677 --> 16:02.293
I'm gonna see
if anyone needs anything.

16:12.806 --> 16:14.889
Well, I don't know
what happened, parthena,

16:14.941 --> 16:17.892
but I don't have any record
of you ever filing
an extension.

16:17.944 --> 16:20.478
Please check
your records again.

16:20.513 --> 16:23.448
Miss parthena filed
more than three months ago.

16:23.483 --> 16:25.566
But she hasn't received
the extension.

16:25.618 --> 16:27.285
Sorry, I can't help you.

16:27.320 --> 16:30.488
Mr. Miller, I put that
application in your hand.

16:30.523 --> 16:31.990
You told me I was good to go.

16:32.025 --> 16:33.825
I don't recall that.

16:33.860 --> 16:34.993
You got a receipt?

16:35.028 --> 16:38.079
You know you ain't
never gave me a receipt.

16:38.131 --> 16:39.998
Not in the 35 years
I've been coming in here.

16:43.503 --> 16:47.138
Miss parthena's usda funds,

16:47.173 --> 16:49.090
they haven't
come through either.

16:49.142 --> 16:50.708
That's why she's been
late with her payments.

16:50.727 --> 16:52.677
Yeah, well,
those funds are tied up

16:52.712 --> 16:55.513
because of the lawsuit
from the white farmers.

16:55.548 --> 16:58.316
You know, it's just not fair
to give folks something

16:58.351 --> 16:59.550
because of their race.

16:59.569 --> 17:01.903
That's reverse discrimination.

17:03.890 --> 17:07.041
Never stopped them from
giving the white farmers
everything they need.

17:07.077 --> 17:11.696
And that lawsuit affects
usda loans, not extensions.

17:14.567 --> 17:17.168
All right.
Well, I'll tell you
what I can do.

17:17.203 --> 17:21.005
Now, I know some folks
that would be very interested
in buying that land of yours.

17:21.041 --> 17:22.356
Okay. He's not gonna help us.

17:22.392 --> 17:24.258
Just hold on a second.

17:25.712 --> 17:28.212
And because I've known you
for nearly 40 years,

17:28.247 --> 17:30.548
I'm gonna make you
an exception.

17:30.583 --> 17:34.902
You get that payment
into this office
within 48 hours,

17:34.938 --> 17:36.921
this whole matter
will be settled.

17:36.940 --> 17:39.891
Where am I gonna
get $25,000 by Monday?

17:41.611 --> 17:43.411
We'll be in touch.

17:43.446 --> 17:44.779
Let's go, miss parthena.

17:48.785 --> 17:50.234
I'll meet you guys in the car.

17:56.275 --> 17:57.942
Excuse me.

17:57.961 --> 17:59.110
You were listening in there.

17:59.129 --> 18:00.545
Yes, I was.

18:02.048 --> 18:03.414
Anything
you can do to help us?

18:04.417 --> 18:06.717
I wish I could,
but it's not my case.

18:06.753 --> 18:08.252
Miller takes
all the black farmers.

18:09.622 --> 18:11.789
He's been slowing down
the process.

18:11.808 --> 18:13.341
-He's waiting out the clock.
-You're right.

18:13.393 --> 18:15.760
Look. Call me.

18:15.795 --> 18:17.461
I can't talk freely here.

18:17.480 --> 18:20.681
Files get lodged with
miller when it comes
to the black farmers.

18:20.717 --> 18:22.299
And he said 48 hours,

18:22.318 --> 18:24.769
but if you could
come up with the money,

18:24.804 --> 18:26.020
best to do it now.

18:26.072 --> 18:28.573
I heard him talking
to the sheriff earlier.

18:28.608 --> 18:30.141
He's not to be trusted.

18:30.160 --> 18:31.776
So be careful.

18:31.811 --> 18:33.111
Give me a call.

18:42.438 --> 18:44.205
Ever been
a friend of black farmers.

18:44.240 --> 18:46.407
Every interview I've done,
miller's name comes up.

18:46.442 --> 18:48.326
Is he the only rep
at the local usda?

18:48.361 --> 18:50.328
Mr. Randolph told me he claims

18:50.380 --> 18:52.730
all the black farm cases
personally.

18:52.765 --> 18:55.166
Easier to control
the system that way.

18:55.218 --> 18:58.336
I know I put that extension
in his hands.

18:58.388 --> 19:00.287
-I swear.
-We believe you.

19:00.306 --> 19:02.507
First, it was ralph angel.
Now this.

19:02.559 --> 19:04.392
The vultures are circling.

19:04.427 --> 19:06.727
If the council votes
to overturn our landmark,

19:06.763 --> 19:07.895
our home is gone.

19:07.931 --> 19:10.598
I got to come up
with $25,000 by Monday.

19:11.451 --> 19:13.067
Otherwise,
I'm gonna lose my farm.

19:13.102 --> 19:14.902
You're not gonna lose
your farm, miss parthena.

19:16.489 --> 19:18.272
If we pool together
all our settlement money,

19:19.576 --> 19:21.809
chip in a little bit
more each,

19:21.828 --> 19:23.811
we can make that payment.

19:23.830 --> 19:25.279
We're not going out
like that this time.

19:26.583 --> 19:27.665
That's my word.

19:29.919 --> 19:31.118
Thank you.

19:39.179 --> 19:42.797
[music playing indistinctly
in background]

19:48.337 --> 19:49.770
uh, excuse me.

19:49.806 --> 19:51.439
Hi. Sorry to interrupt.

19:51.474 --> 19:52.974
I'm looking for zane.

19:53.009 --> 19:54.275
Beige jacket by the shark.

19:54.310 --> 19:55.476
All right. Thank you.

20:04.370 --> 20:05.736
Hey.

20:05.788 --> 20:07.238
Hey.

20:07.290 --> 20:08.656
You must be keke's friend.

20:08.691 --> 20:10.958
Yeah, man. Michael west.

20:10.994 --> 20:12.243
Full disclosure.

20:12.295 --> 20:14.361
I've been a davis west fan
since he first got
in the league.

20:14.380 --> 20:15.529
-Oh, man.
-Yeah.

20:15.548 --> 20:17.748
-Old man was a beast.
-Hey, man. No lies detected.

20:17.800 --> 20:18.966
Yeah.

20:19.002 --> 20:20.167
-I'ma show you around.
-All right.

20:21.537 --> 20:25.039
We're printing out
a few of our favorite
nfts for the walls.

20:25.058 --> 20:29.844
But most of the art lives
in there, in the blockchain.

20:31.547 --> 20:33.180
We only acquire what sells.

20:33.215 --> 20:35.549
And if we bring you
into the ivory nft art show,

20:35.568 --> 20:37.985
you need to sell
and keep selling,

20:38.021 --> 20:39.770
otherwise you're dead weight.

20:39.822 --> 20:40.855
Want a drink?

20:40.890 --> 20:42.657
Yeah, please.

20:42.692 --> 20:43.858
It's got adaptogens.

20:46.246 --> 20:48.779
No booze until the sun sets,
then all bets are off.

20:48.831 --> 20:52.399
All right,
so how do I get into this?

20:52.418 --> 20:57.071
This overprivileged,
totally entitled crew

20:57.090 --> 20:58.739
works on crypto tokens.

20:58.758 --> 21:00.174
-Okay.
-Good vibes.

21:01.243 --> 21:02.677
We're aggregators.

21:02.712 --> 21:04.962
People come to us
because they know
we have real artists.

21:05.014 --> 21:07.748
I mean, here I am.

21:07.767 --> 21:09.750
-Oh, yeah? All right.
-[laughs]

21:09.769 --> 21:11.519
well, first, I need
to take a look at your work.

21:11.554 --> 21:13.187
If it's a fit,
we'll go from there.

21:13.222 --> 21:14.639
-Sounds good.
-My man.

21:14.691 --> 21:15.756
-Let's do it.
-Let's do it.

21:15.775 --> 21:17.525
-Very good to meet you.
-Nice to meet you as well.

21:17.560 --> 21:18.643
-Yeah.
-All right.

21:18.695 --> 21:20.061
-Peace.
-See you.

21:31.774 --> 21:32.873
Mercy.

21:32.909 --> 21:36.227
Looks like
the whole parish turned out.

21:36.262 --> 21:38.946
They think numbers
will make the difference.

21:38.965 --> 21:41.281
We can't afford
a setback here.

21:41.301 --> 21:42.950
We got too much
riding on this.

21:42.969 --> 21:45.119
We'll get them to overturn
the landmark

21:45.138 --> 21:46.921
and finally get the land.

21:46.956 --> 21:48.422
Just let me do my job.

21:57.734 --> 21:59.967
Your mother would be
ashamed of you, baby.

21:59.986 --> 22:02.687
You have no idea
what my mother wants.

22:02.739 --> 22:05.089
All you had to do was get
your nephew to take the deal.

22:05.124 --> 22:06.440
You didn't.

22:06.475 --> 22:08.826
So it's my land now, violet.

22:10.296 --> 22:13.114
I don't give a good goddamn
whose daughter you are.

22:13.149 --> 22:15.149
You watch your tone with me.

22:15.168 --> 22:16.951
I say
let's just go find a seat.

22:18.421 --> 22:19.754
Vi.

22:19.789 --> 22:22.957
I hope your family
is prepared to accept
the council's ruling.

22:22.992 --> 22:24.291
I know we are.

22:28.147 --> 22:29.413
Sam...

22:30.850 --> 22:34.001
Not much is ever in our favor,
never has been.

22:34.020 --> 22:35.519
And we are still here.

22:38.458 --> 22:39.840
We're still fighting.

22:39.859 --> 22:41.392
And we never give up.

22:41.444 --> 22:43.611
You should know that by now.

22:43.646 --> 22:44.945
Come on, daddy.

22:50.370 --> 22:53.654
[people murmuring]

22:57.043 --> 23:01.195
welcome. We're here today
to vote on a proposal

23:01.214 --> 23:05.699
from landry enterprises
to develop an outlet mall
on their land.

23:05.718 --> 23:09.920
This would mean overturning
a historical landmark.

23:09.972 --> 23:13.641
Speaking for the opposition,
nova bordelon.

23:14.977 --> 23:16.343
We'll hear from her now.

23:23.236 --> 23:27.188
This land needs
to remain untouched.

23:27.223 --> 23:28.939
It is the final resting place

23:28.991 --> 23:30.541
for the victims
of the thibodaux massacre.

23:33.896 --> 23:37.031
But it is also my family home,

23:39.902 --> 23:41.168
our home.

23:44.173 --> 23:46.040
My ancestors,

23:46.075 --> 23:48.709
our ancestors have endured
enough suffering in life.

23:50.046 --> 23:54.515
In death, we need to allow
them to rest in peace.

23:54.550 --> 23:56.884
The land was designated
a historical landmark

23:56.919 --> 23:58.052
by the state.

23:59.222 --> 24:01.021
I ask that
the council respect that

24:02.225 --> 24:04.225
and not allow it
to be destroyed for greed.

24:05.561 --> 24:07.228
If we do not honor our past,

24:08.781 --> 24:10.064
we dishonor our future.

24:11.734 --> 24:13.267
Thank you.

24:13.286 --> 24:16.787
[all applauding]

24:23.546 --> 24:24.745
thank you, ms. Bordelon.

24:26.716 --> 24:28.215
And miss campbell.

24:38.060 --> 24:40.427
I too have ancestors
buried on my land.

24:41.564 --> 24:43.764
I too share the pain
of their suffering.

24:45.434 --> 24:48.185
I want to honor those
brave souls

24:48.237 --> 24:50.738
and have them disinterred
and given a proper burial.

24:55.411 --> 24:58.445
This locket was given
to me by my mother.

24:59.982 --> 25:02.032
It was my grandmother's.

25:02.084 --> 25:06.203
She always told me
to remember my ancestors.

25:06.255 --> 25:07.671
And that is what
I am determined to do.

25:09.592 --> 25:13.160
I would be remiss
if I didn't acknowledge
the council

25:13.179 --> 25:15.346
for giving me this opportunity
to speak.

25:18.334 --> 25:19.767
I agree with miss bordelon.

25:21.187 --> 25:23.854
We honor
the past and the future.

25:29.362 --> 25:30.978
[tearfully] excuse me.

25:35.017 --> 25:37.868
We share a deep commitment
to both.

25:42.875 --> 25:46.460
I want to bring life
back to st. Joe.

25:51.133 --> 25:55.920
This development
will create hundreds of jobs,

25:55.972 --> 25:57.805
boosting a weak economy.

25:59.725 --> 26:03.677
It is my honor to bring this
to my mother's hometown.

26:05.848 --> 26:07.147
Thank you for your time.

26:09.018 --> 26:11.352
[all applauding]

26:17.726 --> 26:22.780
st. Joe needs
a financial lift.

26:22.832 --> 26:25.366
Our business community took
a hit due to covid,

26:25.401 --> 26:28.035
and we need
to get back on track.

26:28.070 --> 26:30.120
I move for a vote.

26:30.172 --> 26:33.891
All in favor of keeping
the historical landmark,

26:33.926 --> 26:35.209
raise your hand.

26:49.258 --> 26:52.242
All in favor of removing
the landmark

26:53.779 --> 26:57.231
and going forward
with the landry
development project,

26:58.234 --> 26:59.599
raise your hand.

26:59.619 --> 27:01.902
[people murmuring]

27:07.960 --> 27:09.576
[gavel thuds]

27:15.968 --> 27:17.217
the motion is approved.

27:18.638 --> 27:20.387
The development
will move forward.

27:21.590 --> 27:23.057
The meeting is adjourned.

27:28.431 --> 27:29.930
Did you call him?

27:42.828 --> 27:44.144
The hell is wrong with you?

27:44.163 --> 27:45.696
Like I said,

27:45.748 --> 27:48.666
just trying to bring life
back to a dying town.

27:49.285 --> 27:50.317
It's over.

27:50.336 --> 27:52.252
-You can move the bones.
-Or we will.

27:58.678 --> 28:00.294
Vi.

28:00.329 --> 28:01.628
Excuse us.

28:02.998 --> 28:04.465
Bye, billie.

28:06.469 --> 28:07.801
Hey.

28:09.105 --> 28:11.055
This isn't the end.

28:11.107 --> 28:12.356
Come on.

28:23.085 --> 28:24.685
Oh, baby, we ain't giving up.

28:24.720 --> 28:27.221
But you got to take a minute
to restore and rest up
for a long fight.

28:27.256 --> 28:28.589
Come with me, baby.

28:28.624 --> 28:30.758
Clear skies.

28:30.793 --> 28:33.727
Calm water.

28:33.763 --> 28:39.032
You preoccupied
with all the fishing
you could be doing.

28:39.068 --> 28:41.735
Woman, who's steering
this fantasy, me or you?

28:42.872 --> 28:44.371
I'm sorry. Go ahead.

28:44.407 --> 28:45.672
Thank you.

28:45.708 --> 28:47.457
Where was I?

28:47.476 --> 28:50.944
Oh, yeah.
Nothing for miles.

28:50.980 --> 28:55.682
Just us and the waves,
just all alone.

28:55.735 --> 28:57.818
Hmm.
That sounds like heaven.

29:00.305 --> 29:03.440
You know, I love a full house,
but this...

29:05.661 --> 29:07.528
Just you and me.

29:07.580 --> 29:09.580
You can have me out here
whenever you want.

29:15.955 --> 29:18.372
Even in the worst of times,

29:18.424 --> 29:20.424
we have to remember
our lessons.

29:21.911 --> 29:25.629
Ain't nobody here but me
and these waves.

29:29.602 --> 29:31.885
Catch the other one.
Catch it. Catch it. Catch it.

29:31.937 --> 29:33.971
[both laughing]

29:36.508 --> 29:39.226
♪<i> I got this light</i>
<i> inside of me ♪</i>

29:39.278 --> 29:41.812
♪<i> I follow my heart inside</i>
<i> of me ♪</i>

29:41.847 --> 29:44.481
[music continues indistinctly]

29:47.486 --> 29:48.986
[knocking at door]

29:49.038 --> 29:52.990
♪<i> you wanna be,</i>
<i> I wanna be free ♪</i>

29:53.025 --> 29:57.127
♪<i> I wanna be,</i>
<i> I wanna be me ♪</i>

30:04.887 --> 30:06.036
-hey.
-Hey, bro.

30:06.055 --> 30:07.554
-What's up, man?
-Come in.

30:09.008 --> 30:10.674
-How are you?
-Good.

30:10.709 --> 30:12.326
-How you doing?
-Yo, I'm pretty good, man.

30:12.361 --> 30:14.595
I'm just getting
some work done.

30:14.647 --> 30:16.013
That's not...
That's the good stuff.

30:16.048 --> 30:18.348
Yeah, man.
We had a few bottles
laying around the office.

30:18.383 --> 30:20.317
-Thought you might like it.
-Yeah. Well, yeah.

30:20.352 --> 30:21.935
Come on and make yourself
at home.

30:21.987 --> 30:23.470
Take your shoes off,
if you don't mind.

30:25.674 --> 30:27.024
You want some of this now?

30:27.860 --> 30:29.860
-If you are.
-All right.

30:33.249 --> 30:34.498
Nice.

30:35.251 --> 30:36.617
Great taste.

30:36.669 --> 30:38.902
That's mostly my mom's taste,
but--

30:38.921 --> 30:41.004
charley bordelon west.

30:41.040 --> 30:42.089
She's hot.

30:52.685 --> 30:55.352
So, talk to me, man.

30:55.387 --> 30:58.355
How do I upload a nft?

30:58.390 --> 31:00.307
Like, can I do it

31:00.359 --> 31:02.809
just whenever I want,
wherever I want?

31:02.862 --> 31:05.762
-Like, I don't know the ropes.
-Chill, chill.

31:05.781 --> 31:07.397
Just relax.

31:07.432 --> 31:08.615
Let's take
a look at your photos.

31:09.935 --> 31:11.368
All right, I...

31:13.906 --> 31:15.539
This here...

31:17.126 --> 31:18.375
[computer beeps softly]

31:19.628 --> 31:21.078
-check that out.
-Okay.

31:21.113 --> 31:23.080
You just keep swiping
that way.

31:24.216 --> 31:25.582
To see everything.

31:32.758 --> 31:34.057
This is the heat, man.

31:35.978 --> 31:37.427
This your boyfriend?

31:37.462 --> 31:39.179
No.

31:39.231 --> 31:40.480
Nah. That's just a friend.

31:47.306 --> 31:48.822
Cool.

31:48.857 --> 31:51.241
Now, I know some collectors
that might be interested
in something like this.

31:52.244 --> 31:54.244
-Really?
-Yeah.

31:54.280 --> 31:57.281
But listen, no one sells
the first time out,

31:57.316 --> 31:59.416
so don't get discouraged.

31:59.451 --> 32:01.451
-I'll show you the ropes.
-All right.

32:01.486 --> 32:03.320
-You ready?
-Yeah, I'm ready.

32:03.339 --> 32:05.756
I don't think they ready.
Look at this.

32:05.791 --> 32:07.090
Facts.

32:08.594 --> 32:09.960
[both laughing]

32:09.995 --> 32:12.629
you know, I mean,
she told me her name
was emani.

32:13.799 --> 32:15.933
It helped... It was just vibe.

32:15.968 --> 32:18.685
I mean, I thought she was
just another cool sister.

32:19.972 --> 32:21.188
I can't believe it.

32:23.142 --> 32:25.275
We're not 16 anymore, okay?

32:25.945 --> 32:27.277
We can do better.

32:27.313 --> 32:30.614
-Where's the fun
in that, though?
-[laughs] cheers.

32:32.952 --> 32:34.818
So did you call him?

32:34.853 --> 32:36.236
-I did.
-Mmm.

32:36.288 --> 32:37.371
I did.

32:38.824 --> 32:40.824
-I told him
that I need more time.
-Mmm.

32:41.710 --> 32:44.661
-So emani...
-[laughs]

32:44.696 --> 32:46.380
...Was right. You need
to pull that band-aid.

32:47.466 --> 32:49.466
Yeah, but I still
love him though.

32:52.721 --> 32:56.840
If I let him go, then I'll
never find anybody else.

32:57.643 --> 32:59.476
[sighs]

32:59.511 --> 33:01.979
you know, you've always
had one foot out the door.

33:03.548 --> 33:06.900
Okay. Either step in or out.
Make a choice.

33:08.320 --> 33:09.403
Yeah.

33:13.359 --> 33:14.992
This place has
not changed at all.

33:15.027 --> 33:16.243
Mmm.

33:17.980 --> 33:22.749
The only place we could smoke,
drink, cuss.

33:24.336 --> 33:25.535
Dream.

33:29.341 --> 33:31.675
You know, all you talked about
back then was law school.

33:33.245 --> 33:35.345
What happened?

33:35.381 --> 33:36.546
Life.

33:38.100 --> 33:39.916
I got distracted.

33:39.935 --> 33:41.885
Babies, bills, you know?

33:43.588 --> 33:45.505
I thought I was gonna be
the next pauli murray.

33:45.541 --> 33:48.025
What's stopping you?
You still can.

33:48.060 --> 33:50.093
Stop thinking and just do.

33:50.112 --> 33:51.862
I'ma need you to get
a new catchphrase.

33:51.897 --> 33:53.763
[both imitate gasping
in shock]

33:53.782 --> 33:55.148
it works for me.

33:55.200 --> 33:56.700
Does it?

33:56.735 --> 33:58.235
-Whatever.
-[laughs]

34:05.377 --> 34:07.294
I can't stop thinking about
that council meeting.

34:09.114 --> 34:12.249
I talked to mo earlier,
and she gave me an idea.

34:13.919 --> 34:16.086
We can stage an event
on our land as a protest.

34:21.260 --> 34:25.429
Well, maybe stop thinking
and just do.

34:29.268 --> 34:31.468
-See how I turn that around?
-[stammers] you...

